case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances: On May 16, 1993, the Falls Township Police Dept responded to the area of Rt. 1 South near the Stoney Hill Rd overpass for the report of found human skeletal remains. Detectives responded and found a near complete human skeleton in a drainage ditch a short distance from the roadway. Partial clothing articles were still in tact with the remains. The remains were examined and the deceased could be described as a male, 34-39 years of age, 5'5"-5'7" tall who appeared to be of southern asian or hispanic/mexican-indian decent.
